net.sourceforge.waters.model.base

Class DefaultProxyVisitor

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sourceforge.waters.model.base.DefaultProxyVisitor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ProxyVisitor
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DefaultModuleProxyVisitor, DefaultProductDESProxyVisitor, DescendingProxyVisitor, JAXBModuleExporter, ProxyPrinter

    public abstract class DefaultProxyVisitor
extends Object
implements ProxyVisitor

    An empty implementation of the ProxyVisitor interface.

    This is an adapter class to make it more convenient to implement visitors that do not explicitly implement all the visit methods. All the visit methods in this adapter class do nothing or call the visit method for the immediate superclass of their argument. All these calls eventually trigger the base method visitProxy(), which throws an UnsupportedOperationException.

    A useful visitor is implemented by extending this class and overriding some of the visit methods. As an alternative, consider extending from DescendingProxyVisitor, whose visit methods includes calls to all referenced proxies of the argument.

    Author:
    Robi Malik
